oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Evaluation of Morbidity and Mortality in Young Dairy Heifers After Vaccination with a Pasteurella haemolytica A 1 Leukotoxoid
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Stevens, R. D.
Ellis, R. P.
Camden, D. A.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Respiratory disease
young stock
Pasteurella haemolytica
fibrinopurulent bronchopneumonia
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Respiratory disease is the most common problem in weaned dairy young stock and Pasteurella haemolytica biotype A, serotype 1 is the organism most frequently isolated from the lungs of calves affected with severe, fibrinopurulent bronchopneumonia.
